ilies in America illustrates how family diversity is now the norm. The Sociology in the Twenty-First Century series introduces students to a range of sociological issues of broad interest in the United States today, with each volume addressing topics such as family, race, immigration, gender, education, and social inequality. These books-intended for classroom use-will highlight findings from current, rigorous research and demographic data while including stories about people's experiences to illustrate major themes in an accessible manner. Learn more at www.ucpress.edu/go/sociologyinthe21stcentury.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 16. Mai 2019) 0aFamilies - United States. 0aFamilieszUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / Marriage & Family.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311063539308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2017z978311066755408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCal Press eBook Package Frontlist 2017-2018z978311065859040uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520961241423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520961241.jpg  a978-3-11-063539-3  UC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018  a978-3-11-065859-0  UCal Press eBook Package Frontlist 2017-2018  a978-3-11-066755-4  UC Press eBook-Package 2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles